Ahead of the 2023 general elections, the member representing Potiskum Central Constituency at the Yobe State House of Assembly, Abdullahi Adamu Bazuwa today formally declared his intention to contest for the position Nangere/Potiskum federal constituency of the state. He said he has a burning desire to see a continuous, prosperous, united and equitable constituency. His official declaration ceremony attracted important personalities, politicians, Youth and Women groups, among others showed up solidarity. Addressing the crowd, APC faithful and other supporters, the Ahmed Haruna Daya, legislative aide to the lawmaker said having served Potiskum Central Constituency with development and projects, “he was fully equipped as an administrator, with huge wealth of experience, capacity and energy as well as large heart to accommodate the differences among the people”. Daya who recounted Bazuwa’s numerous achievements as a lawmaker and businessman, describing him as the “Jack of all trade and master of all” that people needs to continue benefiting. He thanked and commended the Executive Governor of Yobe State Mai Mala Buni for the opportunity offered all to serve in various fields which broadened development accross the state. Bazuwa is described by his constituents as a young politician with huge heart of developing and empowering people irrespective of their status.